04/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Presidency Chairman Zeljko Komsic gave NATO Secretary-General Anders Fogh Rasmussen an official request for a membership action plan in Brussels on Friday (October 2nd). "I would like for all Western Balkans countries to be integrated into NATO," Rasmussen said. He added that BiH should implement reforms, especially those related to strengthening democratic institutions, the constitution and the defence sector. The action plan is aimed at preparing candidate countries for full-fledged membership. (RTRS, Dnevni Avaz, Reuters, B92, Tanjug - 02/10/09)
